caption: Pupu heaven! Quick service, accommodating staff & Tasty food. Quick wall from front door to semi-secure parking lot. Check for happy hour!

My fiance and I came here last night, I ordered the chicken thigh and steak fries while my fiance ordered the uni pasta. The service is good as it's quite loud in there, our waters were never empty. My fiance woke up in the middle of the night at around 3am with massive food poisoning which kept us both up on and off all night. Reason I rated this 2/5 is because service was good but I highly recommend this bar to double check their food hazards and standards.

HH drinks include beer, wine by the glass and an assortment of cocktails.  Definitely recommend this place.

I feel a 3 1/2 star is more fitting but rounded it up here.  The service is attentive and the food arrives fast. Parking is right outside.  Love the Happy Hour menu for both drinks & food.  The dishes are overall flavorful, however, some are very salty like the agedashi tofu.  The Uni Pasta is rich in taste, but we couldn't find any uni pieces.  The Clams in White Wine was flavorful, but I wished they were larger clams for a dish that's $18. The garlic bread that goes with it is delicious!  We tried a few more dishes and it definitely fits the bill if you want to hang out late at night & avoid Zippy's at all costs.  It does get very, very, very noisy since it is a bar with a steady flow of customers.  So if you want to catch up with old friends and find out what's going on in their lives, you'll have to yell & repeat yourselves a few times.  Big plus, they do have a vegetarian & vegan menu :D  Overall, it's a nice addition to the Hawaii scene.

Chex Kenzo is located sort of near Keaamoku but on King St. it's near the Bank of Hawaii on that corner. Parking is free on weekends but I don't remember about weekdays. But you could always park on the street too.  The venue is pretty big, probably seat 50 or more. There's a section that can be used for private parties and there is a bar!  The food is Japanese / Italian fusion. I think there's some American stuff as well. They had pasta, agedashi tofu (I totally recommend this!!!), Donburi and many more. The happy hour specials were pretty dang amazing.  They also have their own original drinks but I didn't get a chance to try them. Hopefully next time.  Because it was Japanese mostly, the customer service was on par with Japanese service, where the servers were very polite. I totally like that kind of service.  Definitely recommend for those who like Japanese and Italian food!!!
